<br>
My power-skilling of langauges has always been across North/South Felwithe.<br>
<br>
On that point, it's amazing how even the most dedicated of role-players and &quot;I want to do things the hard way&quot; (I was one of them) players have accepted what is essentially a bug allowing for the learning of languages faster than was designed.  I've yet to hear of anyone who really objects to this method.  I'm curious if anyone does.<br>
<br>
IMHO, an hour or two of real time, zoning and rezoning, makes learning languages hard enough to add flavor to the world.  Certainly examples like Iris are few and far between (people who speak everything) and I still encounter characters constantly that have never learned a language other than their own.  If languages were still as hard as they were designed to be....gah.  I think that early hard limit on 5 points in a foreign langauge destroyed what determinatoin most of us had.<br>
<br>
I know, there is an arguement here against realisism.  But if you can become a master baker in an hour of real time with 20 stacks of batwings and an equivilent amount of fish, why not mastering a language?  I don't see a lot of difference.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
<br>
P.S. Lorec, I've found it reasonably easy to bootstrap two people from the point of one starting with only a single point in the language.  The key is to make sure you both get even, instead of just randomly spamming each other hoping for improvements. You should know who's turn it is to learn next.  Once your skill level is even you zone, one teaches the langauge until there is an improvement, then the other begins.  If you are only watching the screen for the &quot;improved&quot; message you are sure not to miss it.  Takes a second or two longer than the other way, but it prevents confusion and makes for smooth progression.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A> at: 1/3/02 6:44:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fayd>fayd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 8:44:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=914.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bootstrapping....  Can it be done?</span><hr size=1> (ooc)<br>
/agree Valquiss<br>
<br>
I believe that &quot;power learning&quot; the languages is entirely valid  and not an exploit. Just as some tradeskills can be learned quickly with access to platinum, the more common languages can be mastered in a reasonable time. Add in the limited locations where the learning can take place efficiently and the limitation of level ( 5*level + 5 ) and I think the current system works as was probably envisioned by the designers.<br>
<br>
On my slow-zone machine it usually takes more like three to four hours to master a language from zero, and I am not able to do anything else during that time. A good compromise since that may be my entire night's worth of time to play EQ.<br>
<br>
I have also used languages as a welcome gift for new guild members and newbies who are having trouble with the new server rules. They can both get frustrated with the language barriers and since they can often give a master language in return we both win. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/3/02 8:44:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=914.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bootstrapping....  Can it be done?</span><hr size=1> Probably the fastest loading zone of the game is the Arena next to Lake Rathetear.  I zone slower than almost all of my friends, but I can zone in to Arena in about 10 seconds.  Unfortunately Lake Rathetear is a zone of some size and takes considerably longer, but I think it may be the next best option to Felwithe (since many of us are KOS in Felwithe).<br>
<br>
